                              <div class="content-block">
              <h3 class="title"><a href="#"><span>Can you help shape a green future in Atlantic Canada? Join our board.</span></a></h3>
              <div class="content" style="display: none;"><p><strong>Clean Foundation is seeking experienced, committed professionals to serve on our Board of Directors. You’ll join a team working to create a more sustainable society in Atlantic Canada.</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Clean Foundation provides the knowledge, tools and inspiration needed to encourage individual actions that add up to positive environmental change. We are a non-profit, non-governmental organization that works for a clean climate and clean water &#8211; and to help reach these green goals, we foster and support clean leaders.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>We have programs in key environmental areas including energy, water, transportation, waste management and youth engagement to help create a sustainable, vibrant society. Clean was founded in 1988 through an Act of the Legislature in Nova Scotia.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Interested parties should submit their resume by <strong>Friday, May 20, 2016</strong> to:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Scott Skinner, Executive Director</p>
<p><a href="mailto:sskinner@clean.ns.ca">sskinner@clean.ns.ca</a></p>
<p>902.420.3476</p>
